{"build_type":"executable","description":"Minimal placeholder body for a thin PT_INTERP launcher binary. The kernel maps the thin binary and immediately transfers to its PT_INTERP interpreter (our loader), which links the real object closure and runs the real entry; the thin binary's own code never executes. So the launcher only needs a valid, tiny ELF body — this returns 0 and is the body of every object-form tool's thin binary, keeping launchers minimal instead of embedding the tool's full closure.","module_name":"placeholder-launcher-body-for-thin","package_name":"placeholder-launcher-body-for-thin","function_definitions":{"placeholder-launcher-body-for-thin":{"return_type":"i64","parameter_definitions":[],"execution_instructions":[{"instruction_type":"variable_declaration","variable_name":"zero","variable_type":"i64","assignment_operation":"literal","source_target":0},{"instruction_type":"return_statement","return_payload":{"value":"zero"}}]}}}